com.sri.ai.expresso.api

Interface SyntaxTree

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CompoundSyntaxTree, SyntaxLeaf
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSyntaxTree, DefaultCompoundSyntaxTree, DefaultSyntaxLeaf

    @Beta
public interface SyntaxTree
extends java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>
    A Syntax tree (also known as syntactic tree). A syntax tree is either a SyntaxLeaf, or a CompoundSyntaxTree. It has the following properties:
    • value: a non-null Object in the case of Symbols and null in the case of CompoundSyntaxTree.
    • root syntax tree: another syntax tree in the case of CompoundSyntaxTree, and null for Symbols.
    • label: the root syntax tree in the case of CompoundSyntaxTree, and the value in the case of a Symbol.
    • immediate sub-trees: an empty list for Symbol, and a list of syntax trees for CompoundSyntaxTree.

    The interface provides methods for accessing these properties and for setting them. SyntaxTree objects must be immutable, so setting a property returns a distinct syntax tree resulting from the modification.

    Author:
    braz
